Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Lay the @Irish Bacon{130%g} in a single layer on a lined #baking tray{} and bake
on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and crispy, ~{10-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

While the bacon cooks, place a small #pan{} over medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @Almonds{15%g}, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{3-4%mins}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Pop the @Waffles{180%g} (one per person) onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to
warm through, ~{1-2%mins}.

> TIP: You can also warm the waffles in a toaster.

Share the waffle stacks between serving plates, then top with the bacon,
@Blueberries{125%g} and toasted almonds.

Drizzle over the @Maple Syrup{15%g} to finish.